<div><ol><li>Consider each point on a wavefront as a&nbsp;<b>secondary emitter of wavelets</b>.</li><li>The wavelets from each point travels<b>&nbsp;only in the dirction in which the wave is travelling</b>.</li><li>And they&nbsp;<b>combine to form a new wavefront</b>&nbsp;<u>spreading beyond the gap</u>.</li></ol></div>